{"TopicId":205087,"ForumId":24,"TopicTitle":"free power???","CreatedByName":"Garryalways","CreatedById":216534,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-02T09:36:28Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Garryalways","CreatedById":216534,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-02T09:36:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor example, there is a capsule. No forces act on it, but with the help you can spin, rotate. a rocket in space can move if controlled from the keyboard, although the forces do not act on it. how can i disable this feature? *\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James Kerman","CreatedById":160462,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-02T09:45:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelcome to the forum \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/216534-garryalways/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022216534\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/216534-garryalways/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Garryalways\u003C/a\u003E!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe movement you are seeing is from the reaction wheels that are part of most pods. It\u0027s not really free as it uses electrical charge to work. To disable; right click on the pod and either set the wheel authority to 0% or use toggle torque.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022gSGpHQ4.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002289.62\u0022 height=\u0022829\u0022 width=\u0022925\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/gSGpHQ4.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Garryalways","CreatedById":216534,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-02T09:48:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"antipro","CreatedById":173370,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-02T09:59:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit isn\u0027t simpler to disable the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E by pressing the T key? isn\u0027t it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James Kerman","CreatedById":160462,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-02T10:10:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224038726\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205087\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221633168770\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173370\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022antipro\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, antipro said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit isn\u0027t simpler to disable the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E by pressing the T key? isn\u0027t it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E is just a stability and manoeuvre hold function. The reaction wheels will still cause movement unless they are disabled.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"antipro","CreatedById":173370,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-02T10:22:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224038727\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205087\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221633169418\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160462\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022James Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, James Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is just a stability and manoeuvre hold function. The reaction wheels will still cause movement unless they are disabled.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nah ok yes, I got it now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-03T07:42:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder how complicated it would be to make a mod with \u0022reaction wheel authority\u0022 a finite commodity that is drawn upon whenever wheel torque is used. You would build it back up again by expending monoprop.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James Kerman","CreatedById":160462,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-03T09:23:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224039099\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205087\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221633246962\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mikegarrison\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, mikegarrison said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder how complicated it would be to make a mod with \u0022reaction wheel authority\u0022 a finite commodity that is drawn upon whenever wheel torque is used. You would build it back up again by expending monoprop.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReaction wheel saturation or failure would be interesting to deal with.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}